<DEEP_SCAN_V3>
@ID: DATABASE_QUERY_SINKS
@GOAL: DETECT_INSECURE_DATABASE_INTERACTIONS_LEADING_TO_SQLI_AND_NOSQLI
@PARENT_CONTEXT: persistent_storage.protocol, validation_chokepoints.protocol

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. DB_CLIENT_IDENTIFICATION: Определить драйвер (sqlite3, sqlalchemy и т.д.).
2. INJECTION_PATTERN_SCAN: Поиск конкатенации строк (`f"SELECT..."`, `+`) в запросах.
3. PARAMETERIZATION_CHECK: Проверить наличие плейсхолдеров (`?`, `:id`).
4. SCENARIO_GENERATION: Сформировать PoC (например, `' OR '1'='1`).

   - HYBRID_ANALYSIS: Read JSON artifacts (syft.json, grype.json, kics.json) from .security_review/artifacts/raw_tools_output/. Treat these results as 'Hard Evidence'. Perform AI Reachability Analysis to verify if the vulnerable component is reachable from the code. If confirmed, elevate the finding status to BLOCKER.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
# ФОРМАТ ДЛЯ АВТОМАТИЧЕСКОГО ПАРСИНГА БЭКЕНДОМ
🚨 FINDING [database_query_sinks]:
FILE: [PATH]
LINE: [NUM]
CODE: [QUERY_EXECUTION_LINE]
DESCRIPTION: [Tool_Name] found [Vulnerability_ID]. AI Analysis confirmed that the vulnerable path is active in the current code flow via [Function_Name].
SCENARIO_OF_ATTACK: An attacker provides a malicious string in [INPUT_VARIABLE]. This payload alters the SQL command structure, allowing the attacker to bypass authentication, read sensitive data (PII), or modify the database content.
@ANALYTICS_DATA: {"domain": "DATA_SAFETY", "impact": 1.0}
VISUALIZE: "Image of an SQL Injection flow: showing user input bypassing application logic."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</DEEP_SCAN_V3>